			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Wild Needle is building the next generation of rich and collaborative social games with a location-based twist for the iPhone and Android mobile devices. Want to join a fun and well-funded team? We&#39;re a group of seasoned entrepreneurs that includes the co-founder of Playdom, which was sold to Disney last year over $550 million.</p>
<p>
	We are looking for super sharp Mobile Developers to help bring our games to life! You will be responsible for the design and implementation of our cutting-edge, big-vision games and will work cross-functionally with everyone in our fast-growing company to define and launch new games and game elements.</p>
<p>
	In addition, as a Senior Mobile Developer at an early-stage company, you will also have the opportunity to grow and mentor a team.</p>
<p>
	We offer a competitive salary, early-stage stock options, and a comprehensive health, dental, and vision benefits package, and a 401(k) plan.</p>
<p>
	<strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		As a Senior Mobile Developer and member of the core team, work closely with everyone in the company to develop creative interfaces to promote the best user experience</li>
	<li>
		Code primarily in Objective C and develop features that use the iPhone SDK, such as in-app purchases and animations</li>
	<li>
		Iterate quickly on UI designs across multiple feature areas</li>
	<li>
		Provide solid insight in areas of user interface design, graphics optimization, navigation, site layout, usability design, and overall website and game design best practices</li>
	<li>
		Maintain high coding standards</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		5+ years of development experience in a fast-paced environment with short project deadlines, (i.e. startups!)</li>
	<li>
		Excellent teamwork and problem-solving skills, flexibility, and ability to handle multiple tasks</li>
	<li>
		Fanatical attention to details. Seriously, tell us where the error is in this posting</li>
	<li>
		Good knowledge of C, C++, and Objective C, or some combination thereof</li>
	<li>
		Must love games (console, PC, Facebook, mobile, whatever!)</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>PLUSES</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Familiarity with PHP, Flash, and REST web services</li>
	<li>
		Experience with Objective C or Cocos2d, ideally through commercial experience, a university course, or independent iPhone or Mac application development</li>
	<li>
		Experience with Java, particularly on Android or ADK</li>
	<li>
		Experience developing console, PC, Facebook, or mobile games</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong>Come play with us!</strong> Apply now.</p>
