			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Wild Needle is looking for talented 2D/Concept Game Artists to join our growing team. You will work over a wide range of styles and skills and produce both concept and final, in-game artwork, helping us to transform our game concepts to living, breathing experiences. This is an opportunity to be hands on and grow with an early-stage company while making a tremendous impact on a new genre of mobile games.</p>
<p>
	We are a true startup, so you&#39;ll be doing a little of everything -- you might design a new character one minute and create a dozen icons the next.</p>
<p>
	We offer a competitive salary, early-stage stock options, and a comprehensive health, dental, and vision benefits package, and a 401(k) plan.</p>
<p>
	<strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Bring our games and marketing content to life! Conceptualize and create characters, items, environments, and other art assets for game prototypes and production games</li>
	<li>
		Work through ideas from initial sketches to realistic, high-quality finished renderings</li>
	<li>
		Apply a consistent look and feel to all concept and finished artwork</li>
	<li>
		Ensure accuracy of art scope, schedule, and budget</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Excellent drawing skills and a knowledge of anatomy, perspective, composition, lighting, layout, color, and rendering</li>
	<li>
		Ability to deliver preliminary sketches and ideas quickly before finishing approved concepts to a high standard</li>
	<li>
		Experience with a wide range of artistic styles, from realistic/gritty to cute/stylized</li>
	<li>
		Prior experience in game development, either in a studio or as a hobbyist</li>
	<li>
		A real passion for games, virtual worlds, and social networking</li>
	<li>
		Ability to work independently and take ownership of projects in a fast-paced, rapidly-changing environment, often with limited direction</li>
	<li>
		Knowledge of current art production software, tools, and techniques</li>
	<li>
		Expert understanding of art direction and storytelling</li>
	<li>
		Strong attention to detail</li>
	<li>
		Excellent Photoshop skills (CS3-4) compositing, texture painting, tiling, retouch, filtering, scripting</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Come play with us! </strong>Apply now.</p>
