			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Director of Marketing and Business Development</p>
<p>
	The gang at Wild Needle loves games. We also believe that the future of entertainment is free to play, socially connected, and accessible anywhere. We love to be surprised and delighted by our co-workers, and we want to make games that share those great feelings with our audience. If we sound like the kind of people you&rsquo;d like to meet, let us know! And if you&rsquo;re an experienced mobile or online marketer, that&rsquo;s even better. We&rsquo;re looking for someone like you.</p>
<p>
	Wild Needle&rsquo;s Director of Marketing will lead all of the customer acquisition efforts for our games. He or she will work manage budgets across our ad networks, working closely with our Product Managers, analytics team, and CFO to insure we&rsquo;re spending intelligently, measurable, and strategically. He or she will also be familiar with Facebook and other social networks, and will understand how best to leverage them to drive profitable user acquisition. Finally, he or she should be comfortable negotiation mutually beneficial deals with publishing, distribution, and other partners.</p>
<p>
	The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of the dynamics of Facebook and the Apple App Store. He or she will have hands on experience with online marketing, and should feel comfortable with highly measurable marketing. Finally, he or she should love games. Seriously. Doing what you love makes you happy, and being happy makes you fun to be around!</p>
<p>
	In summary, our Director of Marketing will:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Have an analytical mind and real world work experience making data-driven decisions</li>
	<li>
		Have practical experience with Facebook or the App Store&hellip; ideally both!</li>
	<li>
		Possess an expert understanding of online marketing concepts</li>
	<li>
		Understand the free-to-play business model</li>
	<li>
		Have a strong professional network</li>
	<li>
		Have strong verbal and written communication skills</li>
	<li>
		Make mistakes fast, and know how to learn from them</li>
	<li>
		Love to play games</li>
</ul>
